RaspberryPi setup

Recommended Raspberry distribution: Raspbian Lite
Do no enable Windows (graphical user interface) for better performance.

Install required libs on Pi:
---------------------------- 
wget abyz.co.uk/rpi/pigpio/pigpio.tar
 tar xf pigpio.tar
 cd PIGPIO
 make -j4
 sudo make install



Install MSXPi server
-------------------- 
create /home/pi/msxpi/
copy msxpi-server     to /home/pi/msxpi/
copy directory disks  to /home/pi/msxpi/
copy msxpi-client.bin to /home/pi/msxpi/
install systemd (follow instructions in the file)

run msxpi-server manually (if systems is not installed):
---------------------------- 

   cd /home/pi/msxpi
   sudo ./msxpi-server


Kill msxpi-server when auto-started from systemd, and run manually for debug:
---------------------------- 

 sudo killall msxpi-server
 cd /home/pi/msxpi
 sudo ./msxpi-server
 

